@startuml sequence-diagram
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' WorkbenchIQ -- Confidence Scoring sequence diagram
' Target: .NET 8 (ASP.NET Core) + Angular 17+
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
skinparam dpi 150
scale max 1024 width

title Confidence Scoring -- Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Angular\nExtractedFieldsComponent" as FieldsUI
participant "Angular\nConfidenceService" as NgSvc
participant "ASP.NET Core\nConfidenceController" as Ctrl
participant "ASP.NET Core\nConfidenceAnalyzer" as Analyzer
participant "Azure AI\nContent Understanding" as CU
participant "Angular\nConfidenceBadgeComponent" as Badge

== Document Upload & Analysis ==

User -> FieldsUI : Upload document
FieldsUI -> NgSvc : analyzeDocument(file, analyzerId?)
NgSvc -> Ctrl : POST /api/confidence/analyze\n(multipart: file + analyzerId)
Ctrl -> Ctrl : Open file stream from IFormFile
Ctrl -> Analyzer : AnalyzeDocumentWithSummaryAsync(stream, analyzerId, ct)

Analyzer -> CU : Submit document for analysis\n(custom analyzer with confidence)
CU --> Analyzer : Analysis result with\nper-field confidence scores (0-1)

== Field Extraction & Mapping ==

loop For each field in CU response
  Analyzer -> Analyzer : Map to ExtractedField record\n(Name, Value, Confidence, BoundingRegion)
end

== Confidence Categorization ==

Analyzer -> Analyzer : ConfidenceSummary.FromFields(extractedFields)
note right
  Categorize each field:
  - High:   confidence > 0.80
  - Medium: confidence 0.50 - 0.80
  - Low:    confidence < 0.50
  Compute counts and average.
end note

Analyzer --> Ctrl : ConfidenceSummary
Ctrl --> NgSvc : 200 JSON { totalFields, highCount,\nmediumCount, lowCount, fields... }
NgSvc --> FieldsUI : ConfidenceSummary

== UI Rendering ==

FieldsUI -> FieldsUI : Populate sortable table\nwith ExtractedField rows

loop For each field row
  FieldsUI -> Badge : [confidence]="field.confidence"
  Badge -> Badge : Compute level & CSS class
  alt confidence > 0.80
    Badge --> FieldsUI : Green badge "High (92%)"
  else confidence 0.50 - 0.80
    Badge --> FieldsUI : Amber badge "Medium (67%)"
  else confidence < 0.50
    Badge --> FieldsUI : Red badge "Low (34%)"
    FieldsUI -> FieldsUI : Highlight row with\nlight red background
  end
end

FieldsUI --> User : Display extraction results\nwith color-coded confidence

== Optional: Sort by Confidence ==

User -> FieldsUI : Click "Confidence" column header
FieldsUI -> FieldsUI : Re-sort fields ascending/descending\nby confidence score
FieldsUI --> User : Updated table order

@enduml
